ls: List files and directories in the current directory.
pwd: Print the working directory.
cd: Change the current directory.
touch: Create an empty file.
mkdir: Create a new directory.
rmdir: Remove an empty directory.
rm: Remove files or directories.
cp: Copy files or directories.
mv: Move or rename files or directories.
cat: Concatenate and display file content.
less: View text files one page at a time.
head: Display the beginning of a file.
tail: Display the end of a file.
grep: Search for text patterns in files.
find: Search for files and directories.
locate: Quickly find files using a prebuilt index. (sudo yum install locate -->mlocate(name))
tar: Archive and compress files.
zip and unzip: Compress and extract files in ZIP format.
chmod: Change file permissions.
chown: Change file ownership.
ps: Display information about running processes.
top: Monitor system processes in real-time.
kill: Terminate processes.
df: Display disk space usage.
du: Display disk usage of directories.
free: Display system memory usage.
ifconfig or ip: Configure network interfaces.
ping: Test network connectivity to a host.
ssh: Securely connect to remote servers.
scp: Securely copy files between hosts.
wget or curl: Download files from the internet.
date: Display or set the system date and time.
cal: Display a calendar.
who: Show who is logged on.
shutdown and reboot: Shutdown or restart the system.
passwd: Change user password.
useradd and userdel: Add or delete user accounts.
groupadd and groupdel: Add or delete user groups.
sudo: Execute commands with superuser privileges.
su: Switch to another user account.
history: View command history.
man: Display the manual pages for commands.
info: View detailed command information.
lsblk: List block devices.
mount and umount: Mount and unmount filesystems.
df: Display disk space usage.
dd: Copy and convert files.
nc: Network utility for reading or writing data across networks.
awk: Text processing and pattern matching tool.
sed: Stream editor for text manipulation.
cut: Remove sections from lines of files.
sort: Sort lines of text files.
uniq: Remove duplicate lines from a sorted file.
diff: Compare two files or directories.
scp: Securely copy files between hosts.
rsync: Synchronize files and directories between systems.
lsof: List open files and processes.
ncdu: Explore disk usage in a directory.
alias: Create command aliases.
watch: Execute a command periodically and display the output.
crontab: Schedule tasks to run at specific times.
at: Schedule one-time tasks to run at a specific time.
nc: Netcat - networking utility for reading or writing data across networks.
hostname: Display or set the system's hostname.
shutdown: Schedule a system shutdown.
reboot: Reboot the system.
whoami: Display the current username.
groups: Show the groups a user belongs to.
uptime: Display system uptime.
passwd: Change user password.
sudo: Execute commands with superuser privileges.
chroot: Change the root directory.
ssh-keygen: Generate SSH key pairs.
scp: Securely copy files between hosts.
rsync: Synchronize files and directories between systems.
crontab: Schedule tasks to run at specific times.
at: Schedule one-time tasks to run at a specific time.
systemctl: Control and manage systemd services.
journalctl: Query and view system logs.
dmesg: Display kernel messages.
lsmod: List loaded kernel modules.
modprobe: Load and unload kernel modules.
ipconfig or ifconfig: Display network interface configuration.
netstat: Network statistics.
iptables: Manage firewall rules.
route: Display and manage routing table.
hostnamectl: Control system hostname settings.
nmcli: NetworkManager command-line tool.
iwconfig: Configure wireless network interfaces.
psql: PostgreSQL command-line client.
mysql or mysqladmin: MySQL command-line client and administration.
sqlite3: SQLite command-line client.
htop: Interactive process viewer.
iotop: Monitor I/O usage by processes.
atop: Advanced system and process monitor.
killall: Kill processes by name.
nice: Adjust process priority.
renice: Change the priority of running processes.
bg and fg: Manage background and foreground jobs.
jobs: List background jobs.
